        Extracts all concrete features from a feature model by calling extractConcreteFeatures(Iterable) on model.getFeatures().

        Since:

      • extractConcreteFeatures

        public static java.lang.Iterable<IFeature> extractConcreteFeatures(java.lang.Iterable<IFeature> features)
        Extracts all concrete features from an object that yields features. Basically, an invocation of this method on features will return an iterable object that yields a feature f from features if and only if f is concrete. Since the implementation based on iterators, it is a lazy filtering without modification of features.

        The extraction is done via Functional.filter(Iterable, de.ovgu.featureide.fm.core.filter.base.IFilter)
        Parameters:
        features - An iterable object providing features
        Returns:
        An iterable object that yields all concrete features of features
        Since:
        3.0

      • extractConcreteFeaturesAsStringList

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> extractConcreteFeaturesAsStringList(IFeatureModel model)
        Extracts all concrete features from a feature model as a list of strings by calling Functional.mapToStringList(Iterable) on the result of extractConcreteFeatures(IFeatureModel) using model.getFeatures().
        Parameters:
        model - A feature model
        Returns:
        A list of strings that contains the feature names of all concrete features of features
        Since:
        3.0
